commit.message:
The TestCloneableValue test incorrectly tested that the hashCode of the clone should be the same as the original.
The test passed previously because the AltHashCode method based its computation on hashCode.
There is a minor fix to a debugging message (it could NPE or recurse calling hashCode).

JDK-8376512: [lworld] Value objects should consistently use System.identityHashCode
For value objects, the ValueObjectMethods.valueObjectHashCodeAlt uses
System.identityHashCode for all referenced objects.
